'''''The Ballet Class''''' ([[French language|French]]: '''''La Classe de danse''''') is a painting by [[Edgar Degas]], which was painted between 1871 and 1874.<ref name="Musée d'Orsay - La Classe de danse (The Ballet Class)">{{cite web|url=http://www.musee-orsay.fr/en/collections/works-in-focus/search/commentaire/commentaire_id/the-ballet-class-3098.html|title=Musée d'Orsay - La Classe de danse (The Ballet Class)|publisher=[[Musée d'Orsay]]|accessdate=10 January 2015}}</ref> It is in the collection of the [[Musée d'Orsay]], [[Paris]], [[France]].<ref name="Larousse - la Classe de danse">{{cite web|url=http://www.larousse.fr/encyclopedie/oeuvre/la_Classe_de_danse/181368|title=Encyclopédie Larousse en ligne - la Classe de danse|work=Encyclopédie Larousse en ligne|publisher=[[Éditions Larousse]]|language=French|accessdate=10 January 2015}}</ref> It was [[Commission (art)|commissioned]] by [[Jean-Baptiste Faure]].<ref name="Metropolitan Museum of Art - The Dance Class">{{cite web|url=http://www.metmuseum.org/collection/the-collection-online/search/438817?=&imgNo=0&tabName=object-information|title=Metropolitan Museum of Art - The Dance Class|publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]]|accessdate=10 January 2015}}</ref> Degas temporarily abandoned work on this painting, and delivered a [[The Dance Class (Degas, Metropolitan Museum of Art)|work of a similar name]] to Faure.<ref name="Metropolitan Museum of Art - The Dance Class"/>

The painting depicts dancers at the end of a lesson under [[ballet master]] [[Jules Perrot]].<ref name="Musée d'Orsay - La Classe de danse (The Ballet Class)"/> Perrot and Degas were friends, and Degas painted the Dance class in the Paris Operah house a year after it burnt down.<ref name="Larousse - la Classe de danse"/>

